sentences.sContent: They often come up for sale, but this more intimate and later artwork is quite rare and very collectable.
sentences.sContent_eng: They often come up for sale, but this more intimate and later artwork is quite rare and very collectable.
sentences.sCn: 希特勒的画作常被拍卖，但这张卡片显得更为亲切，并且非常罕见，收藏价值很高。

sentences.sContent: Among other things, the collector examines the class loader data structures to determine which classes are live -- that is, are not garbage collectable.
sentences.sContent_eng: Among other things, the collector examines the class loader data structures to determine which classes are live -- that is, are not garbage collectable.
sentences.sCn: 在众多的事情当中，收集器检查类装入器的数据结构，来判断哪个类是活动的 —— 也就是说，不应当被当作垃圾收集的。

sentences.sContent: Another popular method is to buy historic or mint gold coins that, due to their collectable nature, have a value greater than their pure precious metal content.
sentences.sContent_eng: Another popular method is to buy historic or mint gold coins that, due to their collectable nature, have a value greater than their pure precious metal content.
sentences.sCn: 另一个比较流行的方式就是购买历史性的或者数量巨额的金币，由于他们具有的收藏价值，他们往往高于自身金属含量的价值。

words.tran: 集体的；共同的；集合的；集体主义的
可收集的；可回收的（等于collectable）
收集成地；冷静地，镇定地
采集，聚集；[税收] 征收；收藏品；募捐
收藏家；[电子] 集电极；收税员；征收者
集团化；使集体化；使之成为共同的（等于collectivise）

trans.tranOther: something that is collectable is likely to be bought and kept as part of a group of similar things, especially because it might increase in value
